<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>3645</id>
    <title>Sign In: Leaving the self-hosted login screen, it reverts back to WordPress.com login</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">When first opening the app, if you go to the self-hosted login screen, leave the screen (either within the app or by exiting and reopening the app), and the return to the login screen, it will revert back to the WordPress.com login screen.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Steps to reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">1 Open the app while logged out</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">2 Select "Add self-hosted site"</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">3 Optional: begin to enter your account information</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.5">4 Tap on the Help icon (?)</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.6">in the top right, or exit the app on your device</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.7">5 Go back to the login screen</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.8">Result: You see the WordPress.com login screen instead of the self-hosted login screen you were just on</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">I encountered this in a very normal login flow, where I entered my username and site URL but had to leave the app to get my password.</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">When I reopened the app, I saw the wrong login screen.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Tested on Nexus 9, Android 6.0.1, app beta v. 5.0-rc-1.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
